==English==
===Etymology===
* From Spanish ''Filipinas''; from Spanish ''Felipe'', the name of a King of Spain

===Pronunciation===
* fi-li-peeh'-no
* peeh-li-peeh'-noh

===Proper noun===
'''Filipino''' {{m}}, '''[[Filipina]]''' {{f}} (''plural:'' '''[[Filipinos]]''' {{m}}, '''[[Filipinas]]''' {{f}})

# One of two national languages of the [[Philippines]], the other one being [[English]].
# [[nationality|Nationality]] of people born in the [[Philippines]] or residents or citizens of the [[Philippines]].
# [[ethnicity|Ethnicity]] of people identified with the Philippines and its culture and heritage.

====Synonyms====
*(''language'') [[Pilipino]]<!--Wikipedia makes it seem like not quiet a synonym-->
*(''people'') [[Flip]], [[Noypi]], [[Pinoy]], [[Pinay]]

===Adjective===
'''Filipino'''

# Of or pertaining to the [[Philippines]] or its [[people]].
# Of or pertaining to Filipino, the language of the [[Philippines]].

